TITLE: Initializing Direct3D Resources in C++
DESCRIPTION: This method initializes the Direct3D device and creates necessary resources. It sets up feature levels, creates the device and context, and handles device creation flags.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/monaco-editor/blob/main/website/src/website/data/home-samples/sample.cpp.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C++
CODE:
```
void Direct3DBase::CreateDeviceResources()
