TITLE: Error Handling for Identity Results in C#
DESCRIPTION: This helper method processes IdentityResult objects and returns appropriate IHttpActionResult responses. It handles null results, unsuccessful operations, and adds model state errors when available.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/monaco-editor/blob/main/test/manual/samples/run-editor-sample-bom-cs.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
private IHttpActionResult GetErrorResult(IdentityResult result)
{
    if (result == null)
    {
        return InternalServerError();
    }

    if (!result.Succeeded)
    {
        if (result.Errors != null)
        {
            foreach (string error in result.Errors)
            {
                ModelState.AddModelError("", error);
            }
        }

        if (ModelState.IsValid)
        {
            // No ModelState errors are available to send, so just return an empty BadRequest.
            return BadRequest();
        }

        return BadRequest(ModelState);
    }

    return null;
}
```

