TITLE: Querying Employee Data with Exception Handling in PL/SQL
DESCRIPTION: This PL/SQL block performs a SELECT INTO operation to retrieve employee data based on a name. It uses STRICT mode and handles exceptions for no data found or multiple rows returned, raising custom error messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/monaco-editor/blob/main/website/src/website/data/home-samples/sample.pgsql.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PL/SQL
CODE:
```
BEGIN
    SELECT * INTO STRICT myrec FROM emp WHERE empname = myname;
    EXCEPTION
        WHEN NO_DATA_FOUND THEN
            RAISE EXCEPTION 'employee % not found', myname;
        WHEN TOO_MANY_ROWS THEN
            RAISE EXCEPTION 'employee % not unique', myname;
END;
```

