TITLE: Creating PostgreSQL View for Table Metadata
DESCRIPTION: This SQL snippet creates a view named 'tables_vw' that combines information from stv_tbl_perm, pg_class, pg_namespace, and pg_database to provide a comprehensive list of tables across databases and schemas. It includes table IDs, database names, schema names, and table names.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/monaco-editor/blob/main/website/src/website/data/home-samples/sample.redshift.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: SQL
CODE:
```
create view tables_vw as
select distinct(id) table_id
,trim(datname)   db_name
,trim(nspname)   schema_name
,trim(relname)   table_name
from stv_tbl_perm
join pg_class on pg_class.oid = stv_tbl_perm.id
join pg_namespace on pg_namespace.oid = relnamespace
join pg_database on pg_database.oid = stv_tbl_perm.db_id;
```

