TITLE: Implementing nested try-finally blocks with return in C/C++
DESCRIPTION: A function demonstrating nested try-finally blocks with an early return from a finally block. It modifies a counter at different stages to track execution flow. This pattern is not allowed on Windows CE.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/monaco-editor/blob/main/website/src/website/data/home-samples/sample.c.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
#if !defined(WIN_CE) // return from finally not allowed on WinCE
VOID fret(IN PLONG Counter)

{

  try {
    try {
      *Counter += 1;
    }
    finally {
      *Counter += 1;
      return;
    }
  }
  finally { *Counter += 1; }

  return;
}
#endif
```

